Good — contract events are defined inline in the RPC router rather than a service file. Now I have the full picture. Here's the finalized plan:

---

## Final Plan

### Files to modify:

1. **`src/services/client-event-service.ts`** — Add `user.name` join to `listClientEvents`, return `changedByName` in each item
2. **`src/services/task-event-service.ts`** — Same: add user join to `listEvents`
3. **`src/services/prospect-event-service.ts`** — Same: add user join to `listProspectEvents`
4. **`src/rpc/router/client-contract.ts`** — Same: add user join to inline `listContractEvents`
5. **`src/components/audit-logs.tsx`** — New reusable component
6. **`src/routes/(protected)/(app)/clients/$clientId.tsx`** — Use `AuditLogs`, remove inline card, remove `ClientEvent` type

### `AuditLogs` component design:

```tsx
type AuditLogEntry = {
  id: number;
  field: string;
  oldValue: string | null;
  newValue: string | null;
  changedBy: string;
  changedByName: string | null;
  changedAt: Date | null;
};

type AuditLogsProps = {
  entries: AuditLogEntry[];
  domainName?: string;  // "client", "task", etc. for description
};
```

- Renders a `Card` with title "Audit Logs" + `Clock` icon
- Description: `History of changes made to this {domainName}` if provided
- Each entry: `{field}` from `"{oldValue}"` to `"{newValue}"` — by `{changedByName}` — `{timestamp}`
- If `entries.length === 0`, renders nothing

### Backend changes (all 4 event list functions):

For `listClientEvents` (same pattern for others):
```ts
const rows = await db
  .select({
    ...clientEvents,           // all event columns
    changedByName: user.name,  // join
  })
  .from(clientEvents)
  .leftJoin(user, eq(clientEvents.changedBy, user.id))
  .where(eq(clientEvents.clientId, clientId))
  .orderBy(desc(clientEvents.changedAt))
  .limit(limit + 1);
```

Each item will now include `changedByName: string | null` alongside the existing columns.

### `$clientId.tsx` changes:

- Remove `ClientEvent` type
- Remove inline `Card` for events (lines 340-386)
- Replace with `<AuditLogs entries={events} domainName="client" />`
- Keep `ClientDetail` type but it no longer needs `ClientEvent`

